@node Wstëp ".Disclaimer."
         @{b}    )
@{ub}@{i} Disclaimer @{ui}@{b}(
____________/
@{ub}
 @{b}@{i}c64kopik @{ui}@{ub} is a filemanager  to work with Commodore 1541 floppy disk drive.
You need  @{"interface" link Interfejsy}  connecting  this  drive  with  Parallel Amiga Port. I
haven't found  any  other filemanager on Amiga, so  I  decided to fill that
gap - is I managed to do it?

 This program is a GUI for Easy1541 - written by Fabrizio Farenga. It makes
possible  to  connect and using 1541 floppy drive,  however  only from CLI.
c64kopik comfortable and easly can carry out with data on 5'25" floppy.

 Author will not take any responsibility if any damage happen using this
program, however if he using it - cause simply suggestion :F.

@endnode
@node Wymagania ".requirements."
@{b}               )
@{i}@{ub} Requirements @{ui}@{b}(
______________/
@{ub}
@{b}·@{ub} any Amiga with OS 2.04 or better
@{b}·@{ub} intuition.library v37+
@{b}·@{ub} freely distributed @{b}@{i}Easy1541@{ui}@{ub} written by Fabrizio Farenga
  this program is freeware and you can download it from Aminet

@endnode
@node Instalacja ".installation."
@{b}               )
@{ub}@{i} Installation @{ui}@{b}(
______________/
@{ub}
 To install this program just copy all files whenever you want. No assigns
needed. Fonts will be loading just from drawer included in this archive.

 Here you can see all files included with this program:

c64kopik
dat/
   c64kopik.bsh
   c64kopik.cfg
   c64kopik.raw
   fonts/
      playpac.font
      thingPL.font
      playpac/
         8
      thingPL/
         8
docs/
   c64kopik-ENG.guide
   c64kopik-ENG.guide.info
   c64kopik-PL.guide
   c64kopik-PL.guide.info
   interfaceEasy1541.iff
   interfaceFrodo.iff


 Separate question is installation Easy1541:
@{b}·1·@{ub} Put file @{b}iec.library@{ub} in @{b}Libs:@{ub} directory
    in depending of @{"interface" link Interfejsy} there are two libraries available:

  · @{b}Libs/iec.library@{ub} for interface using @{i}@{b}Easy1541 @{ub}@{ui}

  · @{b}Libs/frodo/iec.library@{ub} for interface using emulator @{i}@{b}Frodo @{ub}@{ui}- written by
    Christian Bauer

@{b}·2·@{ub} Put files from drawer @{b}ToolKit@{ub} in @{b}C:@{ub}, that's one:

    IECCmd
    IECDir
    IECLoad
    IECReadD64
    IECSave
    IECStatus
    IECUnit
    IECWriteD64

@{b}·3·@{ub} Put @{b}l/iec-handler@{ub} in @{b}L:@{ub} drawer

 Of course in C: drawer on your system you should have fundamental commands
like @{b}Dir@{ub}, @{b}Copy@{ub}, @{b}Delete@{ub}, @{b}Rename@{ub}, @{b}DiskChange@{ub}, @{b}Mount@{ub}.

@endnode
@node Interfejsy ".interfaces."
            @{b} )
@{ub}@{i} Interfaces @{ui}@{b}(
____________/
@{ub}
 Connecting  floppy  disk  drive  with  Parallel  port  is possible  by two
interfaces.  First  was  work out by Fabrizio Farenga and  it using program
@{i}@{b}Easy1541@{ui}@{ub}. Second interface  is  working with emulator @{i}@{b}Frodo @{ui}@{ub} and  was  done
by Christian Bauer.  Both  schematics are included in documentation of this
programs, so I decided to put it here to compare for your use, dear reader.

@{"interface Easy1541" system "multiview interfaceEasy1541.iff"}
@{"interface Frodo   " system "multiview interfaceFrodo.iff"}

I want to note, that - as like authors of interfaces - I will not take any
responsibility if any damage happen with wrong made cable.

@endnode
@node Obsîuga ".usage."
       @{b} )
@{ub}@{i} Usage @{ui}@{b}(
_______/
@{ub}
 @{b}@{i}c64kopik @{ui}@{ub} is  a  standard  filemanager with two windows. In left window is
printing  directory  of hard disk drive or any volume in AmigaDOS. In right
window  is  listed files from Commodore floppy (volume IEC). All files from
floppy  will  be printing after reading directory. In middle part is a menu
with  options  which  are  enabled  for  both  windows or for only one. For
activate left or right window just click left mouse button on bottom border
where  you can read actual path. If option from menu is enabled - colour of
button  will  be  light blue that means you can use it. If colour of button
will be dark blue - option is disabled. Here is description of commands:

@{b}·drives·@{ub}
Shows any drives and volumes in AmigaDOS.

@{b}·parent·@{ub}
Go to backward drawer.

@{b}·check size·@{ub}
Checking  size  of  file. If selected AmigaDOS files - you will see summary
size  in  blocks.  When  selected  IEC  files, you will see summary size in
bytes.

@{b}·directory·@{ub}
Reading  files  from AmigaDOS if left side window selected or IEC files for
if right side window selected.

@{b}·invert·@{ub}
Selected and non-selected files will be flipped.

@{b}·none·@{ub}
All selected files will be non-selected.

@{b}·copy·@{ub}
Copying  files  on  other  drive. If no free space available, will occur an
error.  If  you  will  copying more files, it's checked only free space for
actually copying file, not for all files.

@{b}·copy as·@{ub}
While copying you can change name of file.

@{b}·rename·@{ub}
You can change name of selected files.

@{b}·delete·@{ub}
Erasing selected files.

@{b}·make copy·@{ub}
Creating on IEC drive an identical copy of file but other name.

@{b}·format·@{ub}
Formatting  IEC  floppy  in two ways: full format and quick format. In full
mode  you  must  enter  new name for floppy and ID number. For quick format
just enter a new name.

@{b}·mount·@{ub}
It's useful to mount IEC for visible in AmigaDOS. You can do any operations
without  using  mount,  using it you will see IEC volume on Workbench, etc.
Then  you  can  reading  directory  by  clicking  on  Workbench  or another
filemanager  or  any  program  but any operations on files is possilbe @{u}only@{uu}
from this program. Is possible to choose device address 8, 9, 10 or 11.

@{b}·makedir·@{ub}
Making drawer in AmigaDOS path.

@{b}·initialize·@{ub}
Initializing device IEC when any error occur with floppy.

@{b}·read d64·@{ub}
This  function make possible to create image of IEC floppy on AmigaDOS disk
in @{i}.d64@{ui} format. Time needed to reading image is about 10 minutes.

@{b}·write d64·@{ub}
This  function  make possible to save image @{i}.d64@{ui} to IEC floppy. Time needed
to saving image is about 10 minutes.

@{b}·execute·@{ub}
Make possible to enter any AmigaDOS command.

@{b}·settings·@{ub}
Program settings, @{"here" link Ustawienia} you find description.

@{b}IEC:real/virtual@{ub}
This  commands  make  possible to create a virtual directory for future IEC
floppy  space.  For  enabled virtual mode, if you select file from AmigaDOS
directory,  this file will list simultaneously on IEC directory. Additional
you  will  see  blocks size, free space on IEC floppy and virtual number of
files.  You  can change order of "virtual" added files by selecting one and
moving  it  by  cursor  keys up-down. Then this files will be saved in that
order when you clicking on left window and select copy option.

@endnode
@node Ustawienia ".settings."
         @{b}  )
@{ub}@{i} Settings @{ui}@{b}(
__________/
@{ub}
 You  can  change any settings from program by selecting option @{i}settings@{ui} or
thru editing file @{b}dat/c64kopik.cfg@{ub}. You can saving or loading from program.
You  can use any options too without saving and back to default settings by
selecting @{b}default settings@{ub} (next you can save or load that settings).

@{b}warnings...@{ub}

 Showing warnings about deleting file.

 no  (0) = don't show
 yes (1) = show (default setting)

 {warnings=0/1}


@{b}reading IEC directory on startup...@{ub}

 Reading IEC floppy when program was started.

 no  (0) = don't read (default setting)
 yes (1) = read

 {iec_startup=0/1}


@{b}operations progress in...@{ub}

 Informations of progress while formatting or creating / saving D64. If you
 want to see progress  of  any  operation,   you can open  a  new window on
 Workbench. If you'll see in this window a prompt @{b}>@{ub}, that means - operation
 done and you can close that window.   You  can  break operations from this
 window by pressing @{b}CTRL+C@{ub}.

 background (0) = don't show progress of operation, do it in background
 new window (1) = show progress of operation in separate window on Workbench
                  (default setting)

 {progress_window=0/1}


@{b}when copied...@{ub}

 After copying a list  of  selected  files you can clear this selections or
 keep it if you would e.g. save that same files on another floppy.

 keep list  (0) = keep a list of selected files
 clear list (1) = clear a list of selected files (default setting)

 {when_copied=0/1}


@{b}open window on...@{ub}

 It's possible to show program on Workbench Screen or in own screen.

 workbench (0) = for now program  will  be  open on Workbench which must be
                 opened in resolution 640x256 or more

 screen    (1) = for now program will  be  open on own screen in resolution
                 PAL:High-Res 640x256 with 16 colours
                 (default setting)

 Changing this option from program will be done  after running program once
 again

 {screen=0/1}


@endnode
@node Problemy ".problems."
          @{b} )
@{ub}@{i} Problems @{ui}@{b}(
__________/
@{ub}
 If any attempt of running program was failed,  then try to open program on
Workbench. For purpose, read configuration file @{b}dat/c64kopik.cfg@{ub} and change
value for {screen} to 0.

If any problems, please contact with @{"me" link Autor}.
@endnode
